BasicIO

Class ASCIIDataFile

  • java.lang.Object
    • BasicIO.ASCIIDataFile

  • public class ASCIIDataFile
extends java.lang.Object
    ASCIIDataFile reads data from tab deliminted text files such as produced by ASCIIOutputFile. There are various read methods in this class. readInt, readDouble, etc Each of these read methods (with the exception of readLine & readC) reads a field at a time returning the data in the field as a type corresponding to the read method. For example readInt returns an int value, and readDouble returns a double value of the field.

    Fields are seperated by tabs and new line markers. Fields are read in sequential order. The first read will read the first field, the 2nd read will read the 2nd field and so forth.

    readLine will return as a String all of the data in the file from the current point to the next newline character. The next read will thus read the first field on the next line. The new line marker is not part of the returned String.

    readC reads raw characters, meaning it will read newline characterers and the tab characters delimiting fields. It doesn't read an entire field, so each readC returns the next character in the field. If a readC is followed by read that reads an entire field, the subsequent read will read the remainder of the field.

    Version:
    1.0 July 08, 2.0 (09/06/30)
    Author:
    A. Cheesman, David Hughes

        public boolean successful()
        Returns true if the last operation was succesfull, false otherwise.
        An operation can fail for several reasons:
        - a read operation was peformed and it is the end of the file. isEOF will return true in this case.
        - a field can not be converted into the specified type, results. isDataError will return true in this case.
        Returns:
        True if last operation was succesfull, false otherwise.
